---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BeforeAfterSlider from '../../components/BeforeAfterSlider.astro';
---

<Layout title="Deck & Fence Washing | Felt Pressure Washing" description="Professional deck and fence cleaning in Eugene, Springfield and surrounding areas. Restore and protect your outdoor wood surfaces.">
  <section class="service-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-icon-lg">ðŸªµ</div>
      <h1 class="section-title">Deck & Fence Washing & Restoration</h1>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Restore and protect your outdoor wood surfaces from weathering</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="service-details">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-row">
        <div class="service-text">
          <h2>Bring Your Wood Back to Life</h2>
          <p>
            Oregon's wet climate is tough on wood. Decks, fences, and pergolas quickly develop moss, algae,
            mildew, and gray weathering that makes them look old and neglected. Left untreated, this buildup
            can actually break down the wood fibers and shorten the life of your structures.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our deck and fence cleaning uses the right pressure and cleaning solutions for the type of wood
            you have. We carefully remove all organic growth and grime without damaging the wood grain,
            leaving surfaces ready for staining, sealing, or just looking great on their own. Ask about our oxadizing brightening add on as well.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="service-slider">
          <BeforeAfterSlider before="/gallery/fences/beforefence-1.jpeg" after="/gallery/fences/afterfence-1.jpeg" altBefore="Deck before washing" altAfter="Deck after washing" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-row">
        <div class="service-text">
          <h3>What We Clean</h3>
          <ul class="service-list">
            <li>Wood and composite decks</li>
            <li>Cedar, pine, and redwood fences</li>
            <li>Pergolas and gazebos</li>
            <li>Railings and balusters</li>
            <li>Outdoor stairs and landings</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="service-slider">
          <BeforeAfterSlider before="/gallery/before-1.jpeg" after="/gallery/after-1.jpeg" altBefore="Fence before cleaning" altAfter="Fence after cleaning" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Will pressure washing damage my deck?</summary>
          <p>Not when done correctly. We use lower pressure settings and fan tips specifically designed for wood surfaces. High pressure can splinter and etch wood, which is why we take a controlled approach. Your deck is in safe hands.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Should I clean my deck before staining or sealing?</summary>
          <p>Absolutely. Cleaning before staining is essential â€” stain won't adhere properly to dirty or mildewed wood. Our cleaning process opens up the wood pores so stain can penetrate evenly and last longer.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can you clean composite decking?</summary>
          <p>Yes. Composite decking still gets dirty and develops algae. We adjust our cleaning method for composite materials, using the right pressure and solutions to clean without damaging the surface.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How often should I have my deck cleaned?</summary>
          <p>In Oregon's climate, we recommend cleaning your deck annually. This prevents moss and algae from taking hold and keeps the wood in good condition. If your deck is in heavy shade, twice a year may be beneficial.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do you offer staining or sealing after cleaning?</summary>
          <p>Our focus is on the cleaning and preparation. We can recommend trusted local professionals for staining and sealing, or discuss options when we're on-site.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="service-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Ready to Restore Your Deck or Fence?</h2>
        <p>Get a free estimate today â€” no obligation, no pressure.</p>
        <a href="/#estimate" class="btn btn-primary">Get Free Estimate</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .service-hero {
    padding: 60px 0 30px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #F0F9FF 0%, #E0F2FE 100%);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .service-icon-lg {
    font-size: 48px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .service-details {
    padding: 50px 0;
  }

  .service-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 40px;
    align-items: start;
    margin-bottom: 50px;
  }

  .service-row:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .service-text h2 {
    font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--dark-gray);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .service-text h3 {
    font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--dark-gray);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .service-text p {
    color: var(--light-gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    font-size: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .service-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .service-list li {
    padding: 10px 0;
    padding-left: 28px;
    position: relative;
    color: var(--dark-gray);
    font-weight: 500;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB;
  }

  .service-list li::before {
    content: 'âœ“';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--success);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .faq-section {
    padding: 50px 0;
    background: var(--bg-light);
  }

  .faq-list {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .faq-item {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    border: 1px solid #E5E7EB;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: box-shadow 0.3s ease;
  }

  .faq-item:hover {
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  }

  .faq-item[open] {
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    border-color: var(--light-blue);
  }

  .faq-item summary {
    padding: 18px 24px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--dark-gray);
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    font-size: 16px;
  }

  .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .faq-item summary::after {
    content: '+';
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--primary-blue);
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-left: 16px;
  }

  .faq-item[open] summary::after {
    content: 'âˆ’';
  }

  .faq-item p {
    padding: 0 24px 18px;
    color: var(--light-gray);
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 15px;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .service-cta {
    padding: 50px 0;
  }

  .cta-block {
    text-align: center;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary-blue), var(--accent-blue));
    color: var(--white);
    padding: 48px 40px;
    border-radius: 16px;
  }

  .cta-block h2 {
    font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .cta-block p {
    font-size: 18px;
    opacity: 0.9;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 968px) {
    .service-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 30px;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .service-hero {
      padding: 60px 0 30px;
    }

    .service-text h2 {
      font-size: 24px;
    }

    .cta-block {
      padding: 40px 24px;
    }

    .cta-block h2 {
      font-size: 24px;
    }

    .faq-item summary {
      font-size: 15px;
      padding: 16px 20px;
    }

    .faq-item p {
      padding: 0 20px 16px;
      font-size: 14px;
    }
  }
</style>
